{"key":"post-12058725","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12058725</id>\n<content>I'm currently inoculating well over 1000 lbs of rye berries per month, and do it all with grain to grain transfers.&amp;nbsp; The main reason is if I inoculate 400 spawn bags with LC and it turns out bad, I've just lost 1500 pounds of pressure cooked grains.&amp;nbsp; When doing g2g where one bag inoculates ten more, if one transfer goes bad, I only lose a maximum of ten bags.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Grains inoculated with other grains will take off faster than with LC.&amp;nbsp; Where LC shines is in not waiting the ten days for a bag to colonize before using it for g2g.&amp;nbsp; However, when doing a lot of bulk, the risk factor is too great with LC, thus I don't use it.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12059516</next>\n<prev>12058480</prev>\n<first>12055702</first>\n<last>12063769</last>\n<when>1266592621</when>\n<utime>02/19/10 05:17 PM</utime>\n</post>"}